â–¶ï¸ How to Run the Project
python chatbot.py

Console Flow:

Enter a website URL (or press Enter for default)

Website content is scraped and analyzed

Chatbot starts interaction

Ask questions related to the website

Type exit or quit to stop

ğŸ’¡ Example Interaction
Enter the website URL to scrape:
https://botpenguin.com/

Jarvis: Hi! I have analyzed the website.
Ask me anything about it!

You: What services does this website provide?
Jarvis: The website offers AI chatbot solutions for businesses...

ğŸ§  How It Works (Architecture)
Step-by-Step Flow:

Website Scraping

Fetches HTML using requests

Parses content using BeautifulSoup

Removes scripts, styles, headers, footers

Text Cleaning

Removes extra spaces

Limits text to 3000 words

Context Injection

Website content is added as a system message

ChatGPT is instructed to answer strictly from this data

Conversation Loop

User questions are appended to chat history

GPT generates contextual responses

ğŸš§ Limitations

Cannot answer questions outside website content

Console-based UI (no web UI)

Depends on website accessibility

Token limits for very large websites

